    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for that. so when people talk about the \"trickle-down\" aspect, is there any actual consensus on whether those growth benefits actually reach the lower income brackets, or is that mostly just theoretical? i'm trying to figure out if the data actually supports that view or if it's just a common talking point.",
